<dl id="n36205g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36205g">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36205g"> 205(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Klonvocation</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Ku Kluxism.]</font> H.W. Evans, Imperial Wizard, <cite>The Klan of Tomorrow and the Klan Spiritual</cite>, p.17. At the end of the pamphlet containing it are these words: &ldquo;During the delivery of this address the great audience of men sat in silence, as though entranced. At its conclusion the <mark>Klonvocation</mark> arose quietly and stood in reverential spirit. Someone started &ldquo;Onward, Christian Soldiers&rdquo; and the song was joined in by the deeply impressed men.&rdquo; This is at the Klonvocation of 1924 at St. Louis. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 259 n3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
